<subSubSection id="C3428CD9FFEEFFBBFF27CF9EFDA57337" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE7DF52FFEEFFBBFF27CF9EFDA57337" blockId="6.[151,1436,1511,1824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="B92C0340FFEEFFBBFF27CF9EFE9F7370" bold="true" box="[151,273,1511,1536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A moderately elongate species with yellow face, partly yellowish pleuron, and blackish abdomen without fasciae of golden pile. Smaller (
<quantity id="4CA072B7FFEEFFBBFDECCC72FD227353" box="[604,684,1547,1571]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) and more compactly built than the similarly coloured, larger (
<quantity id="4CA072B7FFEEFFBBFAC1CC72FF697337" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13– 14 mm</quantity>
) and more elongate 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A4D1FFEEFFBBFE7CCC49FDAB7337" box="[460,549,1584,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sava">
<emphasis id="B92C0340FFEEFFBBFE7CCC49FDAB7337" box="[460,549,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">M. sava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
